title: 820-3435 - Minor Liquid Damage, dead
message:
820-3435 - Minor Liquid Damage, dead

It was actually on when I got it. Shut it down for inspection and it hasn't come back on since. SMC Reset changes the magsafe light, and PPBUS is 8.6v.

There was corrosion on U8005, and C8005 right beside it. I replaced both. 

I have PPBUS, PP3V42_G3H, PPVRTC_G3H, PP5V_S5. 

I'm missing PP5V_S4RS3. Missing PP3V3_SUS at BIOS, and missing SUS_EN as well.

At this point I'm beyond my limited expertise with power issues. Thanks for any advice!

title: 820-3435 - Minor Liquid Damage, dead
message:
Check PCH's RTC signals, PM_DSW_PWRGD and PCH_DSWVRMEN.
Also check PM_BATLOW_L.
Do you get 3V3_S5?

title: 820-3435 - Minor Liquid Damage, dead
message:
If S5_PWRGD is high, PM_DSW_PWRGD should go high too.
This signal is controlled by SMC, but I suppose the pull-up resistor is inside PCH.
Heat PCH area until 180-200 degrees, for 15-20s; use quality flux, not chinese honey.
